26'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|7.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Maria Mutola]]|MOZ|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2:04.36'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|8.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Sheila Seebaluck]]|MRI|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2:08.93'''\n|}\n<br>\n{| border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"2\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"cccccc\"\n!RANK\n!style=\"width: 20em\"|HEAT 3\n!style=\"width: 5em\"|TIME\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|align=\"center\"|1.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Sigrun Wodars]]|GDR|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2:02.24'''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|align=\"center\"|2.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Delisa Walton-Floyd]]|USA|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2:02.37'''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|align=\"center\"|3.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Soraya Telles]]|BRA|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2:02.48'''\n|- style=\"background:#ddffdd;\"\n|align=\"center\"|4.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Dalia Matuseviciene|Dalya Matusevi\u010dien\u0117]]|URS|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2:02.57'''\n|- style=\"background:#ddffdd;\"\n|align=\"center\"|5.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Kirsty Wade]]|GBR|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2:02.75'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|6.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Maureen Stewart]]|CRC|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2:08.17'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|7.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Laverne Bryan]]|ANT|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2:12.18'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|\u2014\n|{{flagIOCathlete|Sun Sumei|CHN|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|'''DNS'''\n|}\n<br>\n{| border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"2\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"cccccc\"\n!RANK\n!style=\"width: 20em\"|HEAT 4\n!style=\"width: 5em\"|TIME\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|align=\"center\"|1.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Kim Gallagher]]|USA|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2:01.70'''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|align=\"center\"|2.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Diane Modahl|Diane Edwards]]|GBR|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2:01.79'''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|align=\"center\"|3.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Nadiya Olizarenko]]|URS|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2:01.81'''\n|- style=\"background:#ddffdd;\"\n|align=\"center\"|4.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Letitia Vriesde]]|SUR|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2:01.83'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|5.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Hassiba Boulmerka]]|ALG|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2:03.33'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|6.\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Ren\u00e9e Belanger]]|CAN|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''2:04.74'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|\u2014\n|{{flagIOCathlete|Rosa Colorada|ESP|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\"|'''DNS'''\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[1987 World Championships in Athletics \u2013 Women's 800 metres|1987 Women's World Championships 800 metres (Rome)]]\n* [[1990 European Championships in Athletics - Women's 800 metres|1990 Women's European Championships 800 metres (Split)]]\n* [[1991 World Championships in Athletics - Women's 800 metres|1991 Women's World Championships 800 metres (Tokyo)]]\n* [[Athletics at the 1992 Summer Olympics - Women's 800 metres|1992 Women's Olympic 800 metres (Barcelona)]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{in lang|en}} [http://www.la84foundation.org/6oic/OfficialReports/1988/1988v2.pdf Official Report]\n\n{{Olympics800metres}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Athletics At The 1988 Summer Olympics - Women's 800 Metres}}\n[[Category:Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics|8]]\n[[Category:800 metres at the Olympics]]\n[[Category:1988 in women's athletics]]\n[[Category:Women's events at the 1988 Summer Olympics]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Olympic event\n|event = Women's 800 metres\n|games = 1988 Summer\n|image =\n|caption =\n|venue = [[Olympic Stadium (Seoul)|Olympic Stadium]]\n|dates = {{Date|1988-9-24}} (heats)<br />{{Date|1988-9-25}} (semi-finals)<br />{{Date|1988-9-26}} (final)\n|competitors = 29\n|nations = 19\n|win_value = 1:56.10\n|longnames = yes\n|gold = [[Sigrun Wodars]]\n|goldNOC = GDR\n|silver = [[Christine Wachtel]]\n|silverNOC = GDR\n|bronze = [[Kim Gallagher]]\n|bronzeNOC = USA\n|prev = [[Athletics at the 1984 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 800 metres|1984]]\n|next = [[Athletics at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Women's 800 metres|1992]]\n}}\n{{AthleticsAt1988SummerOlympics}}\n\nThe '''[[800 metres|Women's 800 metres]]''' at the '''[[Athletics at the 1988 Summer Olympics|1988 Summer Olympics]]''' in [[Seoul, South Korea]] had an entrylist of 29 competitors, with four qualifying heats (29) and two semi-finals (16), before the final (8) took off on Monday September 26, 1988.<ref name=\"SR\">{{cite web |url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/summer/1988/ATH/womens-800-metres.html |title=Athletics at the 1988 Seoul Games: Women's 800 metres |accessdate=21 October 2017 |work=sports-reference.com}}</ref>\n\n==Medalists==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\" text-align:center; font-size:110%;\" width=\"35%\"\n|-\n|{{OlympicGoldMedalist|[[Sigrun Wodars]]|GDR|1988 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicSilverMedalist|[[Christine Wachtel]]|GDR|1988 Summer}}\n|-\n|{{OlympicBronzeMedalist|[[Kim Gallagher]]|USA|1988 Summer}}\n|}\n\n==Records==\nThese were the standing world and Olympic records (in minutes) prior to the 1988 Summer Olympics.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:95%;\"\n|- \n! World Record\n| 1:53.28\n| {{flagicon|TCH}} [[Jarmila Kratochv\u00edlov\u00e1]]\n| [[Munich]] ([[West Germany|FGR]])\n| July 26, 1983\n|-\n! Olympic Record\n| 1:53.43\n| {{flagicon|URS}} [[Nadiya Olizarenko]]\n| [[Moscow]] ([[USSR|URS]])\n| July 27, 1980\n|}\n\n==Summary==\nThe final started with returning silver medalist [[Kim Gallagher]] running the fastest first turn to take the lead at the break.  But that was short lived as the two East German teammates ran past her down the backstretch, [[Christine Wachtel]] on the inside, leading [[Sigrun Wodars]] tight on her shoulder.  [[Inna Yevseyeva]] moved to the outside to run past Gallagher, with [[Slobodanka \u010colovi\u0107]] in her wake while Gallagher had her teammate [[Delisa Walton-Floyd]] a step behind her.  As Yevseyeva moved forward, the first lap was a fast 56.43.  Through the penultimate turn, Wodars took the lead and pushed the pace.  Behind her, a break began to form as Walton-Floyd, [[Maite Z\u00fa\u00f1iga]] and [[Diane Edwards]] couldn't keep up.  Wachtel made up a little lost ground on the backstretch and pulled shoulder to shoulder with Wodars by the 600 mark in 1:25.5, then taking the lead into the final turn.  It was a lead in formality only as Wodars, Yevseyeva and \u010colovi\u0107 lining up in close order drill, getting ready to pounce coming off the turn.  As the straightaway neared, Gallagher seized the gap on the inside, running through to Wachtel's heels.  Yevseyeva struggled to keep up, as Gallagher moved to the outside of Wodars, leaving \u010colovi\u0107 with nowhere to run and the first three all having clear running room to the finish line.  Just like the [[1987 World Championships in Athletics \u2013 Women's 800 metres|World Championships]] the year before, Wachtel had a slight edge coming off the turn and a long history of winning, but in the big ones, Wodars had slightly more speed to edge ahead and take the gold even more decisively.  The race lost, Wachtel struggled toward the end but Gallagher couldn't catch her for the silver.\n\n==Final==\n{| border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"2\" cellpadding=\"5\" style=\"border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 90%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"cccccc\"\n!RANK\n!style=\"width: 20em\"|FINAL\n!style=\"width: 5em\"|TIME\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|[[Image:Med 1.png]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Sigrun Wodars]]|GDR|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''1:56.10'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|[[Image:Med 2.png]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Christine Wachtel]]|GDR|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'''1:56.64'''\n|-\n|align=\"center\"|[[Image:Med 3.png]]\n|{{flagIOCathlete|[[Kim Gallagher]]|USA|1988 Summer}}\n|align=\"center\" |'