{"title_page": "Milen Tsvetkov", "text_new": "{{short description|Bulgarian TV host}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Milen Tsvetkov\n| image              = https://glas.bg/news/2020/04/19/milen-tsvetkov-zagina-pri-zhestoka-938.jpeg\n| alt                = Photo of Milen Tsvetkov\n| birth_date         = {{birth date |1966|7|30}}\n| birth_place        = {{nowrap|[[Sofia]], Bulgaria}}\n| death_date         = {{death date and age|2020|4|19|1966|7|30}}\n| death_place        = {{nowrap|[[Sofia]], Bulgaria}}\n| death_cause        = [[Car accident |Car accident]]\n}}\n'''Milen Tsvetkov''' ({{lang-bg|\u041c\u0438\u043b\u0435\u043d \u0426\u0432\u0435\u0442\u043a\u043e\u0432}}) (July 30, 1966 - April 19, 2020)<ref name=\"baharova\">{{cite news|url=http://temanews.com/index.php?p=tema&iid=233&aid=5874|title=\u0414\u0430 \u0441\u0435 \u0441\u044a\u0431\u0443\u0434\u0438\u0448 \u0441 \u041c\u0438\u043b\u0435\u043d \u0426\u0432\u0435\u0442\u043a\u043e\u0432|last=\u0411\u0430\u0445\u0430\u0440\u043e\u0432\u0430|first=\u041f\u0435\u0442\u044f|date=November 2011|publisher=\u0422\u0435\u043c\u0430|language=Bulgarian|accessdate=23 June 2011}}</ref> was a [[Bulgaria]]n [[journalist]] and [[TV host]].<ref name=\"24chasa\">{{cite news|url=http://www.24chasa.bg/Article.asp?ArticleId=369189|title=\u041c\u0438\u043b\u0435\u043d \u0426\u0432\u0435\u0442\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u0441 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u043e \u043f\u0440\u0435\u0434\u0430\u0432\u0430\u043d\u0435 \u0432 \u041d\u0422\u0412|publisher=24 \u0447\u0430\u0441\u0430|language=Bulgarian|accessdate=23 June 2011|date=5 February 2010}}</ref>\n\nTsvetkov was born in [[Sofia]].<ref name=\"baharova\"/> From March 2011 to July 2018, he was the host of his own talk show on [[Nova Television (Bulgaria)|Nova Television]], titled ''Milen Tsvetkov's Hour''.<ref name=\"standart\">{{cite news|url=http://paper.standartnews.com/bg/article.php?article=359447|title=\u041c\u0438\u043b\u0435\u043d \u0426\u0432\u0435\u0442\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u043f\u0430\u043a \u043f\u0440\u043e\u0432\u043e\u043a\u0438\u0440\u0430 \u0432 \u041d\u043e\u0432\u0430 |date=2011-03-03|publisher=\u0421\u0442\u0430\u043d\u0434\u0430\u0440\u0442|language=Bulgarian|accessdate=23 June 2011}}</ref> In 2008, it was announced that he would be the new host of the fourth season of [[Big Brother 4 (Bulgaria)|Big Brother]] (airing on the same channel), replacing former host [[Niki Kunchev]] for only one season. He died at age 53 in a car crash accident in Sofia.<ref name=\"avtora\">{{cite news|url=http://www.avtora.com/news/nowini/milen_cwetkow_e_nowiyat_wodesht_na_big_brother_4|title=\u041c\u0438\u043b\u0435\u043d \u0426\u0432\u0435\u0442\u043a\u043e\u0432 \u0435 \u043d\u043e\u0432\u0438\u044f\u0442 \u0432\u043e\u0434\u0435\u0449 \u043d\u0430 Big Brother 4|date=2008-07-07|publisher=Avtora.com|language=Bulgarian|accessdate=23 June 2011}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n{{Use dmy dates|date=January 2012}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Tsvetkov, Milen}}\n[[Category:1966 births]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian television personalities]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian television presenters]]\n[[Category:2020 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Sofia]]\n[[Category:Road incident deaths in Bulgaria]]\n{{Bulgaria-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Bulgarian TV host}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name               = Milen Tsvetkov\n| image              = https://glas.bg/news/2020/04/19/milen-tsvetkov-zagina-pri-zhestoka-938.jpeg\n| alt                = Photo of Milen Tsvetkov\n| birth_date         = {{birth date |1966|7|30}}\n| birth_place        = {{nowrap|[[Sofia]], Bulgaria}}\n| death_date         = {{death date and age|2020|4|19|1966|7|30}}\n| death_place        = {{nowrap|[[Sofia]], Bulgaria}}\n| death_cause        = [[Car accident |Car accident]]\n}}\n'''Milen Tsvetkov''' ({{lang-bg|\u041c\u0438\u043b\u0435\u043d \u0426\u0432\u0435\u0442\u043a\u043e\u0432}}) (July 30, 1966 - April 19, 2020)<ref name=\"baharova\">{{cite news|url=http://temanews.com/index.php?p=tema&iid=2